  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-05-13",
    "date": "2020-06-11T17:18:48Z",
    "text": "Limiting Infant Fatality and Empowering Nonprofit Organization Workforces or the LIFE NOW Act\n\nThis bill modifies the Paycheck Protection Program, established to support small businesses in response to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019).\n\nSpecifically, the bill expands the program to encompass any nonprofit organization regardless of size, and it strikes the affiliation requirements applicable to nonprofit organizations and veterans organizations.\n\nThe bill also makes any entity that provides abortions ineligible to receive a paycheck protection loan. An exception is allowed for abortions performed at hospitals or if the pregnancy is the result of rape or incest or endangers the life of the mother."
  },
